Anonymous Sat 22 Feb 2020 19:48:47 No.28533241 Report
Quoted By: >>28534440
>>28532147
Power exchange.
If the female starts dominant, that trait must be relevant to the plot as well as the story's conflict. Her internal relationship/struggle with it needs to change.
Likewise, a character that evolves into dominance needs a reason for it.
This is a prime reason why attribute waving characters often fail. There's little use amplifying a character's LBGT profile unless the story revolves around it. Same for feminist or fetish fiction. Just saying "He's gay" or "She's dominant" doesn't show the why.

Does every element in-story have to further the character development? No, but if you're unwilling to write about conflict then don't tiptoe deeply into bdsm topics.

The idea of having a blank Anon character is a deliberate way around it. Done wrong it's lazy. Done right, the writer starts manipulating the reader into being an active part of the story, fleshing it out themselves from the implications provided.

Anonymous Sun 23 Feb 2020 07:02:47 No.28546051 Report
Quoted By: >>28549822
>>28530890
You should be fine as long as you don't request too fast. I think I pulled a little under 300 threads including images from them at one point, with no issues at all.

Here are a few pointers to hopefully help you get started on this project.

Getting a list of OPs:
https://desuarchive.org/_/api/chan/search/?board=trash&type=op&text=hmofa&page=1

Keep increment the page parameter until you've got all the OP ids. This API will return stuff in JSON, so just find a JSON library and get to work.

Once you've got ids:
http://desuarchive.org/_/api/chan/thread/?board=trash&num=<thread #>

Replace thread number with a thread id that you got from the previous step, and repeat for every id you found. JSON returned is a list of posts with every attribute you need for that thread.

Storing all that and converting it to a format that's easily readable is a big problem, with several projects dedicated to it. I previously solved it by adapting some of the archival code already out there. Regardless, good luck.
